# 6. 手ごわい子供達

Honami: We're looking forward to putting on a great event with all of you today!
Honami: We're still novice storytellers, but we promise to do everything we can to make sure all the children go home smiling today.
Nene: We look forward to working with you.
Association Chair: Likewise! You both really saved the day by agreeing to do this.
Association Executive A: We heard that you've prepared a number of effects. We're really looking forward to seeing them!
Nene: Oh...
Nene: Yes, we promise to do our best!
Association Executive A: Wonderful! Anyway, we'll see you two again a little later.
Nene: I was a little worried that I'd be overstepping since I'm an outsider...
Nene: But they all seem really happy to have me.
Honami: Hehe. They're very grateful for you, Kusanagi.
Nene: I see...
Honami: Still, time really flew by while preparing for this event. I can't believe it's already the day of.
Nene: Me neither. I'm actually feeling a little more nervous than I usually do before I go out and perform.
Honami: Hehe. Me too.
Honami: (I asked quite a lot of people for their help, and I did everything I could to prepare for this event, but...)
Honami: (Will I manage to do this story justice?)
Nene: Oh, the children should be arriving soon...
Honami: You're right. Why don't we make sure all the equipment works one last time?
Nene: Then, I'll check the stuff over by the stage.
Honami: Okay, I'll see you again in a bit.
???: <Sounds like it's almost showtime, Honami.>
Honami: MEIKO...?!
MEIKO: <Hehe. I'm sorry if I startled you. But I wanted to tell you something before your reading.>
Honami: Tell me something...?
MEIKO: <Yes. I actually watched your rehearsal yesterday in secret.>
MEIKO: <You two were so good that you had me on the edge of my seat the whole time!>
Honami: I really appreciate you saying that...
Honami: I was a little worried that the children wouldn't enjoy the way we present this story...
Honami: But I feel much better after hearing you say that you liked what you saw, MEIKO.
MEIKO: <As with any live performance, it's normal to have a lot of things go through your mind...>
MEIKO: <Chiefly, whether or not all the hard work you put in is going to pay off.>
MEIKO: <But I'm sure you two will do just fine. So, go out there and have as much fun as the children are about to.>
Honami: Thank you! I'll do just that, MEIKO.
Honami: I'll find a good spot by the stage for my phone, so please stay and watch if you like.
MEIKO: <Thank you! I'll be rooting for you.>
Nene: The people at registration seem to be done. I guess that's everyone?
Honami: Yes, we'll probably be introducing ourselves very soon.
Honami: Let's do our best today, Kusanagi...
Nene: Yeah, we gotta make the most of all the hard work we put in.
Association Chair: Alright, it's time for today's fun and fantastic reading event to begin.
Children: Yay! What do you think they're gonna read today?
Children: I dunno, but I'm really excited...!
Association Chair: Today, these two lovely ladies will be your storytellers.
Honami: Hello, everyone. We hope you're looking forward to today's story.
Children: Huh? Where's our usual storyteller?
Honami: We're sorry about that. But we promise to do our best today so that you all have fun.
Children: Okay...
Nene: Umm... Would you all mind sitting down in front of the stage for us?
Children: I'm gonna be first!
Children: Hey, no fair! I wanna be first!
Association Executive B: Cut it out, you two. There's plenty of space for everyone.
Children: Okay.
Nene: Then, can you kids also...?
Children: Tag! Hehe. You're it!
Children: Hey, wait!
Nene: W-Wait! Stop running around and come over by the sta—
Children: Heehee. Catch me if you can!
Children: Haha. Too slow!
Nene: Th-They're too fast...!
Nene: Phew... They finally agreed to sit... Wait—
Children: Cool, we did it! Hey, you guys! Let's play up here!
Nene: How did he get on stage?!
Honami: I'm sorry, but we need to use the stage when telling the story, so could you come back down?
Children: No!
Nene: N-No...?
Association Executive A: Oh dear... They're usually a little less rambunctious than this.
Nene: They are?
Children: Well, duh! Our usual storyteller isn't here! And these two look like wimps.
Children: They're super slow, too.
Nene: What was that?
Honami: K-Kusanagi...!
Nene: I know... They're just kids being kids.
Nene: Everybody, come on down here...
Children: We don't wanna!
Nene: You little...
Association Executive B: Hey, you children need to listen to them!
Association Executive A: Otherwise, you won't be getting any snacks later.
Children: Grr... Fine...
Nene: Are you sure we're gonna be okay...?
Honami: I'm a little less certain now...
